Henry HEDRICK, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 6248. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 10, 1931. E. A. Ewald, of Great Palls, Mont., for appellant. Wellington D. Rankin, U. S. Atty., and Howard A. Johnson and Arthur P. Acher, Asst. U. S. Attys., all of Helena, Mont.

Before RUDKIN, WILBUR, and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to motion of appellant, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
